#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cfeatures%5Coutput-formats.md:1
msgid "Output Formats"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cfeatures%5Coutput-formats.md:3
msgid ""
"The `format` query parameter on `/rules/{rule_id_path}` selects the "
"serialisation of the response. Seven values are accepted."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cfeatures%5Coutput-formats.md:7
msgid "cprmv-json (default)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cfeatures%5Coutput-formats.md:9
msgid ""
"A custom recursive JSON format produced directly from rdflib's graph "
"traversal, not from RDF serialisation. The response is a nested dictionary "
"that mirrors the `cprmv:hasPart` tree of the rule:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cfeatures%5Coutput-formats.md:11
msgid ""
"{\n"
"    \"https://standaarden.open-regels.nl/standards/cprmv/0.4.0/#id\": "
"\"Artikel 20\",\n"
"    \"https://standaarden.open-regels.nl/standards/cprmv/0.4.0/"
"#definition\": \"...\",\n"
"    \"https://standaarden.open-regels.nl/standards/cprmv/0.4.0/#hasPart\": "
"{\n"
"        \"lid 1\": {\n"
"            \"https://standaarden.open-regels.nl/standards/cprmv/0.4.0/"
"#id\": \"lid 1\",\n"
"            \"https://standaarden.open-regels.nl/standards/cprmv/0.4.0/"
"#definition\": \"...\",\n"
"            \"https://standaarden.open-regels.nl/standards/cprmv/0.4.0/"
"#hasPart\": {\n"
"                \"onderdeel a\": { ... }\n"
"            }\n"
"        }\n"
"    }\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cfeatures%5Coutput-formats.md:27
msgid ""
"All sub-rules contained via `cprmv:hasPart` RDF lists are recursively "
"included. Predicate URIs are used as keys."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cfeatures%5Coutput-formats.md:29
msgid ""
"!!! note When `unformat` is also provided, the format is forced to `cprmv-"
"json` regardless of the `format` value. The named fields extracted by the "
"`parse` pattern are merged into the top-level JSON object."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cfeatures%5Coutput-formats.md:34
msgid "RDF formats"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cfeatures%5Coutput-formats.md:36
msgid ""
"For all non-`cprmv-json` formats, the API serialises the [Concise Bounded "
"Description (CBD)]{1} of the matched rule node using rdflib's serialiser:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cfeatures%5Coutput-formats.md:38
msgid "`format` value"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cfeatures%5Coutput-formats.md:38
